    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2933257417" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2933257417" />
    <a title="Ayunda" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2053190-ayunda"><img alt="Ayunda" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1544690760p2/2053190.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2933257417?book_show_action=true">Aug 19, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ayunda" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ayunda" href="/user/show/2053190-ayunda">Ayunda</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780330492997" href="/book/show/829793.The_Voice_of_the_Violin">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2053190-ayunda?shelf=translated">translated</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2933257417" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5887386455153899019">Set in Sicily and focusing on our grouchy, irritable main character Inspector Montalbano, in this fourth book of the series (and my first book I&apos;ve ever read in the series) we follow him and his team as he &quot;accidentally&quot; discovers a dead woman in a squeaky clean house.<br/><br/>I have never before read an Italian book and it&apos;s such a pleasure to read this small little mystery novel. It&apos;s quaint and the setting as well as the way of life of the characters here are very European that it makes me want to go </span>
  <span id="freeText5887386455153899019" style="display:none">Set in Sicily and focusing on our grouchy, irritable main character Inspector Montalbano, in this fourth book of the series (and my first book I've ever read in the series) we follow him and his team as he "accidentally" discovers a dead woman in a squeaky clean house.<br /><br />I have never before read an Italian book and it's such a pleasure to read this small little mystery novel. It's quaint and the setting as well as the way of life of the characters here are very European that it makes me want to go back to Italy. I love the small details of the Inspector's love for pasta, his relationship and his personal life scattered here and there in the story, and the different pace of the story compared to conventional crime novels.<br /><br />The crime itself for me is also interesting, though certainly a little forgettable. Maybe it's because of the many Italian names that makes it hard for me to follow who is who, but also because I keep waiting for the violin to appear in the story and it would only appear much much later in the book. Overall it was the characters that shined in the book.<br /><br />I look forward to reading more books in the series. I have <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/30968.Excursion_to_Tindari__Inspector_Montalbano__5_" title="Excursion to Tindari (Inspector Montalbano #5) by Andrea Camilleri" rel="nofollow noopener">Excursion to Tindari</a> next up and I'm excited to acquire more books in the series and get to know more about mister Montalbano and his crew!</span>
  <a data-text-id="5887386455153899019" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

